{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-08-07-3",
 "title": "A Jog and a Quiet Investigation",
 "summary": "At dusk on Caspar, Representative Eva Sargent takes one of her rare jogs, trailed by two bodyguards, when the Intelligence officer Bazil McKenzie -- now formally uniformed and far removed from his old casual Ghost Squadron days -- falls in beside her. After introductions, Bazil reveals he is quietly investigating John Donivan, the immensely powerful head of the First Bank, and probes Sargent about how much influence the magnate holds over the New Republic. Sargent, who has dealt with Donivan in diplomatic circles, acknowledges his sway over foreign policy and concedes it is plausible he bribes military, diplomatic, and Senate figures. When Bazil presses whether such corruption could be prosecuted, she lists possible charges -- campaign violations, conspiracy, tax crimes -- while cautioning that the facts must first be known, before Bazil thanks her and vanishes into the shadows.",
